---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="No Lock-In Printer's editorial policy for source handling, product recommendations, corrections, and speculative hardware coverage."
>
  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Editorial policy</p>
    <h1>We separate confirmed facts from buying advice and speculation.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Printer ownership claims can change with firmware, regional model variants, and supply availability. Our editorial policy is designed to keep that uncertainty visible.
    </p>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>Source standards</h2>
      <p>
        We prefer official manufacturer pages, driver documentation, support articles, standards documentation, reputable technical coverage, and clearly labeled user reports. Unverified claims are not treated as final buying advice.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>Product recommendations</h2>
      <p>
        Recommendations emphasize ownership risk: subscription requirements, ink or toner economics, driver support, local printing options, and firmware behavior. Commission potential does not determine whether a product appears in a guide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        If a page has outdated pricing, model support, driver information, or product status, contact us with a source. We update pages when the evidence materially changes the buying decision.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
